()1. Yeh Kya Hai Aur Kaun Banata Hai?
Yeh Java ki ek inbuilt library (java.lang) ka hissa hai. 
Ise tum (Developer) import karte ho jab tumhein runtime par (yaani jab code chal raha ho)
kisi Java Class ke Constructor ko dynamic tareeqe se access karna ho aur uska object banana ho, bina new ClassName() likhe.
 
()3. Live Code Implementation in SailPoint:-
Maan lo tumhare paas ek custom helper class hai jiska naam hai CustomLoggerHelper. 
Aur is class ka ek constructor hai jo ek argument leta hai: SailPointContext context.
Ab tum direct new CustomLoggerHelper(context) nahi likhna chahte, balki runtime par reflection ke through iska object banana chahte ho.

()Pehle Dekho Custom Class Kaisi Dikhrahi Hai:-
Java
package com.custom.utils;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;

public class CustomLoggerHelper {
    private SailPointContext context;

    // Yeh hai woh constructor jise hum reflection se call karenge
    public CustomLoggerHelper(SailPointContext context) {
        this.context = context;
    }

    public void logMessage(String msg) {
        // Tumhara custom logic
        System.out.println("IIQ Custom Log: " + msg);
    }
}

()Ab Dekho SailPoint Rule/Beanshell Mein Reflection Ka Code:-
Yahan hum java.lang.reflect.Constructor ka use karenge.
->>
import java.lang.reflect.Constructor;
import sailpoint.api.SailPointContext;

try {
    // 1. Class ko uske fully qualified name se load karo
    Class targetClass = Class.forName("com.custom.utils.CustomLoggerHelper");

    // 2. Batao ki constructor kis type ka parameter leta hai (Yahan yeh SailPointContext.class leta hai)
    Class[] constructorArgs = new Class[] { SailPointContext.class };

    // 3. Constructor object fetch karo (Yahan java.lang.reflect.Constructor kaam aata hai)
    Constructor constructor = targetClass.getConstructor(constructorArgs);

    // 4. Runtime par parameter pass karke naya instance (object) create karo
    // 'context' variable SailPoint ke har rule mein implicitly available hota hai
    Object helperInstance = constructor.newInstance(new Object[] { context });

    // 5. Ab tum is object ka method dynamic call kar sakte ho ya cast karke use kar sakte ho
    if(helperInstance != null) {
        // Method invoke karne ke liye (Simple casting approach agar class classpath mein hai)
        com.custom.utils.CustomLoggerHelper helper = (com.custom.utils.CustomLoggerHelper) helperInstance;
        helper.logMessage("Bhai, reflection chal gaya successfully!");
    }

} catch (ClassNotFoundException e) {
    log.error("Class nahi mili bhai: " + e.getMessage());
} catch (NoSuchMethodException e) {
    log.error("Aisa koi constructor nahi mila: " + e.getMessage());
} catch (Exception e) {
    log.error("Reflection mein kuch bafda hua: " + e.getMessage());
}
